==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Placentation
<hw>Plac`en*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The mode of formation of the placenta in
different animals; <as>as, the <ex>placentation</ex> of
mammals</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The mode in which the placenta is
arranged or composed; <as>as, axile <ex>placentation</ex>; parietal
<ex>placentation</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placentiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
